# Radstash — Cursor Rules
# These rules help Cursor (and Claude) understand the project architecture.
# Drop this in the project root as .cursorrules

## PROJECT OVERVIEW
Radstash is a cross-platform collectibles management + anonymous marketplace app.
Comics, trading cards, sneakers, fashion, coins, jewelry, vinyl, art — any collectible.
Users scan items with AI, track values, and trade on an anonymous auction marketplace.

- **Framework**: Expo (React Native) with expo-router (file-based routing)
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict)
- **Platforms**: Web (localhost:8081), iOS, Android
- **Backend**: Firebase Auth + Storage, Supabase (Postgres + Edge Functions)
- **AI**: Claude Vision API for item identification
- **Data**: Comic Vine API for cover images, PriceCharting affiliate for pricing
- **Design System**: Material Design 3 color roles + custom vault dark aesthetic

## TECH STACK

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Framework | Expo ~52, expo-router ~4 |
| UI | React Native, StyleSheet (no Tailwind) |
| Icons | @expo/vector-icons (MaterialIcons) via `lib/icons.tsx` |
| Theme | 3 modes: Dark, Light, High Contrast via `hooks/useTheme.tsx` |
| State | React useState/useContext (local, no Redux) |
| Auth | Firebase Auth (configure in .env) |
| Database | Supabase (PostgreSQL + RLS) |
| Storage | Firebase Storage (photos, EXIF stripped) |
| Realtime | Supabase Realtime (live bids) |
| AI | Anthropic Claude Vision via Edge Function |
| Covers | Comic Vine API (free, 200 req/hr) |
| Payments | Stripe Connect (Phase 3) |

## FILE STRUCTURE

```
collectors-vault/
├── app/                        # expo-router screens
│   ├── _layout.tsx             # Root layout — wraps ThemeProvider
